WEBVTT


00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.740
If this is your first Christmas away from your children,

00:00:03.320 --> 00:00:08.280
and you are dreading it and truly don't know how you're gonna make it,

00:00:08.281 --> 00:00:10.421
I want you to know you're gonna make it.

00:00:11.080 --> 00:00:14.140
I have four kids. One of them has down syndrome.

00:00:14.160 --> 00:00:17.420
She had her first open heart surgery at 4 days old.

00:00:18.080 --> 00:00:19.880
She almost died several times.

00:00:19.881 --> 00:00:21.481
They had to resuscitate her back to life.

00:00:21.482 --> 00:00:23.221
And when she was finally discharged,

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:25.860
they said, Mrs. Templeton,

00:00:25.920 --> 00:00:27.520
this child at one time

00:00:27.521 --> 00:00:31.561
was ten times sicker than even the sickest child in this hospital.

00:00:31.562 --> 00:00:33.521
The cancer unit, the burn unit,

00:00:33.522 --> 00:00:34.801
anywhere you look in this hospital,

00:00:34.802 --> 00:00:37.121
she was 10 times sicker than their sickest kid.

00:00:37.122 --> 00:00:40.101
And I did not think she was ever gonna make it.

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:43.480
And I but almost fucking broke down when he told me that.

00:00:43.481 --> 00:00:45.921
Cause I was like, you reassured me this whole time,

00:00:45.922 --> 00:00:47.161
and I was trusting in your words,

00:00:47.162 --> 00:00:48.921
and you didn't even believe in your own fucking words.

00:00:48.922 --> 00:00:50.501
But she was. She made it.

00:00:51.040 --> 00:00:52.440
She's now in middle school.

00:00:52.441 --> 00:00:55.481
She's fine. She's had many other heart surgeries and other things.

00:00:55.482 --> 00:00:57.021
But what I'm saying is, like,

00:00:57.800 --> 00:00:59.600
I understand feeling like. No,

00:00:59.601 --> 00:00:59.961
no, no,

00:00:59.962 --> 00:01:00.321
no, no,

00:01:00.322 --> 00:01:00.921
no, no, no.

00:01:00.922 --> 00:01:04.481
You don't get it. I don't know how I'm gonna make it

00:01:04.482 --> 00:01:08.741
if I don't see and hold my children on this day that, like,

00:01:08.800 --> 00:01:10.900
is motherhood. Like who.

00:01:10.920 --> 00:01:12.780
Who is Santa? Mom.

00:01:13.160 --> 00:01:15.360
Who makes the magic, the Christmas Magic?

00:01:15.361 --> 00:01:16.961
Mom, what do you work?

00:01:16.962 --> 00:01:18.321
So hard. All year long.

00:01:18.322 --> 00:01:20.361
All year long, you're using Santa as an excuse.

00:01:20.362 --> 00:01:23.081
And then this one day is the day that you don't get to see your kids.

00:01:23.082 --> 00:01:27.141
And you know that somebody else is taking joy and pleasure in that.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:27.800
They're.

00:01:27.801 --> 00:01:32.261
They're not gonna enjoy the day the way that you would enjoy the day.

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:33.440
The. So you.

00:01:33.441 --> 00:01:34.501
You know what I mean?

00:01:34.960 --> 00:01:38.560
And you're pissed that they're doing it to take it away from you,

00:01:38.561 --> 00:01:41.581
not to enjoy it. That's. Do you know what I mean?

00:01:44.080 --> 00:01:47.240
You're super valid in feeling all the hurt feelings.

00:01:47.241 --> 00:01:49.241
And I think the more you try to escape them,

00:01:49.242 --> 00:01:51.081
the more they chase you. So

00:01:51.082 --> 00:01:53.941
you need to just spend a good amount of time crying

00:01:54.040 --> 00:01:55.420
and feeling like shit

00:01:56.080 --> 00:01:56.640
and, like,

00:01:56.641 --> 00:01:59.821
checking in with yourself and see what do you need.

